cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.GT 

This paper deals with a multi-armed bandit problem, which is a classic problem in machine learning and optimization. The paper focuses on developing a new algorithm for this problem and analyzing its performance. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves decision-making and game theory concepts, which make cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) possible categories as well.
